text: This movie actually had a pretty great concept and for most of it, actually executed it pretty well. However the ending dropped the ball pretty hard.    It actually gave me a pretty lovecraftian feel. How it made the people go mad at just learning the name(Which in my opinion is one of this films greatest blunders. Seriously the "bye bye man"?, You'd of had a better job by just writing some gibberish and saying it's impossible to say correctly in human words, with NARKUSHAFU or some bs as the human way of saying it. That being thrown aside, I actually really enjoyed the fact that the monster didn't actually kill anyone. It just made the people it infected go mad and kill each other. This unstoppable force that just hearing the name will cause you and anyone else you mention the name go mad as well.   Kinda reminds me of a worse executed Grudge in some ways now that I think on it.
